00:00:17.579 --> 00:00:21.000
One is, several people were
wondering, how

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:25.416
does the cell decide whether to
do mitosis or meiosis?

00:00:25.416 --> 00:00:28.643
But the
mitosis, which is ordinary cell

00:00:28.643 --> 00:00:31.500
division is what happens
everywhere

00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:33.858
in your body,
in your intestine,

00:00:33.858 --> 00:00:35.760
on your skin,
in your eye,

00:00:35.760 --> 00:00:38.897
anywhere
except, since thats how you

00:00:38.897 --> 00:00:42.000
make all the different cells you
have.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.253
The meiosis,
which creates the sex sells,

00:00:44.253 --> 00:00:46.833
or gametes, happens in a very
specific place,

00:00:46.833 --> 00:00:50.000
either in the testes if you are
male or the ovary if you

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:50.825
are a female.

00:00:50.825 --> 00:00:54.000
So, there's a dedicated place
where meiosis takes

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:57.696
place, and just your knowledge
of human anatomy and physiology

00:00:57.696 --> 00:01:00.142
can
make a pretty good guess as to

00:01:00.142 --> 00:01:01.142
where that is.

00:01:01.142 --> 00:01:03.759
Everywhere
else, it's mitosis.

00:01:03.759 --> 00:01:07.000
There's a very special place
where

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:08.164
that happens.

00:01:08.164 --> 00:01:13.000
A couple of you still got
confused when I was talking

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:17.885
about meiosis and I was showing
you a progression through,

00:01:17.885 --> 00:01:20.875
and I put a
double headed arrow,

00:01:20.875 --> 00:01:25.000
meaning that's what that period
was called.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:27.727
The process is unidirectional.

00:01:27.727 --> 00:01:29.909
It only goes in one way.

00:01:29.909 --> 00:01:32.826
It's not a
reversible process.

00:01:32.826 --> 00:01:36.384
There were some questions about
the

00:01:36.384 --> 00:01:40.198
